{"kind":"symbol","identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/com.mapbox.MapboxMaps\/documentation\/MapboxMaps\/TileStoreUsageMode\/readAndUpdate"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Tile store enabled for accessing local tile packs and for loading new tile packs from server."}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["iOS"],"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"case"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"readAndUpdate"}]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"discussion","type":"heading","text":"Discussion","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"All tile requests are converted to tile pack requests, i.e."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"the tile pack that includes the request tile will be loaded, and the tile extracted","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"from it. In this mode, no individual tile requests will be made.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"This mode can be useful if the map trajectory is predefined and the user cannot pan","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"freely (e.g. navigation use cases), so that there is a good chance tile packs are already loaded"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"in the vicinity of the user.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If users can pan freely, this mode is not recommended. Otherwise, panning","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"will download tile packs instead of using individual tiles. Note that this means that we could first","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"download an individual tile, and then a tile pack that also includes this tile. The individual tile in","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the disk cache won’t be used as long as the up-to-date tile pack exists in the cache.","type":"text"}]}]}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLangu